<subSubSection id="F902AE7FE9E1FA1A8BA0CA72DE58D999" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="6EA2E6897D7EC1A52F601EE80795311F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4498EAEC447B9D92DEF015292F75FCFE" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="D5EC2DA2966E20FD7DDFB8105041D54B" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Oecanthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Oecanthus fultoni" order="Orthoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fultoni">
<emphasis id="24D2C6AA28C975C24E0F89500F927E20" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Oecanthus fultoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a new record from Umerkot, Desert Thar, Pakistan. This species is reported from 
<taxonomicName id="51BB3FCFE1A1D85B1CF16C3AFEBDD942" genus="Cynadon" lsidName="Cynadon dactylon" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="dactylon">
<emphasis id="F9B1BA0BD2FF41CC6EC1CE790D90585A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Cynadon dactylon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(common lawn grasses) surrounded by wild plants.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E2034951F448EE1A1A8313090498F934" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8F72FFCA0499D60C10EADD9E97C04AD5" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Global distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DBDFDBFBD2C58DAC5A88BAD552D8DA63" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Ohio, Franklin, New Jersey, Washington, Pakistan (
<bibRefCitation id="C4169322294C852EF76CD2F73D6D6805" author="Cigliano, MM" journalOrPublisher="The Zoological Survey of India, Calcutta" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="http://Orthoptera.SpeciesFile.org" refId="B6" refString="Cigliano, MM, Braun, H, Eades, DC, Otte, D, 2020. Orthoptera species file online, version 5.0/5.0. http://Orthoptera.SpeciesFile.org" title="Orthoptera species file online, version 5.0 / 5.0." url="http://Orthoptera.SpeciesFile.org" year="2020">Cigliano et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F514131400781111340F66A84DCB7823" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="3DE70D2A4711F70E762DF2FA221C40C5" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4364F50BAFF5839F70BC3F77E3686024" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<bibRefCitation id="2BC48BE58C9BF62B752E3C46A77FC119" author="Walker, TJ" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="157 - 161" refId="B27" refString="Walker, TJ, Gurney, AB, 1967. The metanotal gland as a taxomonic character in Oecanthus of the United States. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington 69: 157 - 161" title="The metanotal gland as a taxomonic character in Oecanthus of the United States." volume="69" year="1967">Walker and Gurney (1967)</bibRefCitation>
observed differences between populations of this species from the coasts of western and eastern USA showing that 
<taxonomicName id="3FA21390AF0BFA4BE17303FBB65BE09F" genus="O." lsidName="O. fultoni" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="fultoni">
<emphasis id="DA94E5AF08A909175E987FBD77313D5B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">O. fultoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
displays variations in the structure of the metanotal gland.
</paragraph>
